---
description: YUBI Supervision project conventions for agents
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `AGENTS.md` before making changes. For architecture or scaling decisions, also read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.

- Keep `backend/main.py` thin; vision orchestration in `backend/vision.py`; YUBI v3.0 in `gemini_vision.py`; expressions in `expression_vision.py`; session reports in `session_report.py`.
- Never block the FastAPI event loop with camera, model init, or GenAI — use `VisionEngine` background threads or worker threads for report streams.
- Webcam capture is server-side OpenCV; macOS camera permission applies to the Python process.
- Use env-based settings via `backend/config.py`; update `.env.example` and docs when adding variables.
- User-facing branding: **YUBI v3.0** (not vendor model names in UI or exports). Internal code may use `gemini_*` env vars.
- After editing `frontend/app.js`, run `node --check frontend/app.js` — syntax errors break Initialize.
- Do not commit `.venv/`, `.env`, `*.pt`, or `backend/models/*.task`.
